I really like the notebook organizer of Multi-Edit.  However, I wanted it to
adjust to the size of the display and show more text and topics and stuff.
So, with this in mind, I called Tech Support and American Cybernetics and
Aaron told me what to look for.  Armed with this information, I made the
following changes:


        1.  Made the main display screen adjust to the size of
            the screen display.  If the screen is 43 characters
            tall, the main display is 40 (screen_length - 3).
            This change also was made in the text editing area.

        2.  Made the main and edit screens full 80 columns of the
            screen.  This allows the displays to be wider and the
            text edit screen to edit more text.

        3.  Added a Spell check button to the edit text screen.
            This will only work if you have the Professional
            version of Multi-Edit.

        4.  With all of the screen size adjustments, I moved the
            fields and buttons to adjust with the screens.


Thought about additions but never made:

        1.  Have the windows adjust automatically to the screen
            width in addition to the screen height.

        2.  Export to a 'DBF' file layout (I didn't think long
            about this one!)

I would like to hear any feedback regarding my changes and if you like them.

